commit.message:
Fixed issue #110: Removed validation for certain settings

We can't validate the presence of the settings below because these can
be detected by boto by using the AWS instance metadata service.

AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY, AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID, AWS_SESSION_TOKEN

Technical discussion in issue 110:
https://github.com/etianen/django-s3-storage/issues/110

commit.message:
Drop support for Django < 2.2

As a side effect this also remove support for Python 2.7 since Django
1.11 was the last release of Django that supported Python 2.7.
Python 2.7 will reach its EOL in 1,5 months anyway.
https://pythonclock.org/

Django 2.2 is a LTS release and exists for over half a year, so it's
time to drop support for the previous LTS release, Django 1.11.

Django 2.0 is already past its EOL since April 2019.

Django 2.1 will reach its EOL in about a month.
